# Database Build and Organization

## Prisma schema standards
- Keep canonical models in `prisma/schema.prisma` only.
- Model role-backed users via `User` + role tables (`Teacher`, `Student`, `Admin`) with explicit relations.
- Use cascade delete only where domain-safe and expected.
- Use composite keys for join-like data (`Grade` on `[assignmentId, studentId]`) when uniqueness is pair-based.

## Type and client generation
- Keep generated client output stable (`src/app/generated/prisma`).
- Ensure install/build flow regenerates client (`postinstall`/build step).
- Use a singleton Prisma client in `src/lib/prisma.ts`.

## Seed architecture
- Keep seed data split by domain under `prisma/seeds/data`.
- Keep seed scripts deterministic and idempotent where possible.
- Separate raw data constants from seed execution logic.

## Query contract hygiene
- Use `select`/`omit` to avoid returning sensitive or irrelevant fields.
- Convert DB objects to safe UI/domain shapes before returning from actions.
